summaries.short: A hospice program is introduced into the ward; Dawn looks ahead to her future; Patsy becomes a patient.
summaries.full: DiDi takes on greater responsibilities when a hospice program is introduced into the ward. Dawn looks ahead to her future and tries to share her news with Patsy, but inadvertently puts his new initiative in question. Patsy finds himself playing patient when he has a medical emergency. An alcoholic patient named Dottie looks for ways around the doctor's orders.

summaries.short: The staff goes 'old school' after a server crash; DiDi faces a long day.
summaries.full: A server crash forces the staff to go 'old school'--with disastrous results. DiDi steps on Dr. Stickley's toes when making a decision about Arlene's mother-in-law, while Dr. James has issues getting through to a deaf patient. Dawn buys herself a cello, and learns her life-changing news may not be what it seems.

summaries.short: Season Two Premiere. Dr. James fights for her research; DiDi asks for a raise; Dawn searches for answers.
summaries.full: Season Two Premiere. Dr. Jenna James' plethora of research projects threatens to take over the ward. A frustrated DiDi asks for a raise; Patsy's 'Lean Green' initiative causes problems; Dawn gets a surprising answer to what's been ailing her. Later, Jenna gets some unwelcome news that leads her to make an unholy alliance.

summaries.short: A leaked photo creates privacy issues for the ward; DiDi finds herself tempted; Patsy and Dawn reach a crossroad.
summaries.full: The staff finds itself in an awkward situation when one of Jenna's 'adult' study photos mistakenly makes its way into the Christmas Card Competition. DiDi is tempted by Parker Owens, a visiting doctor. Denya, a patient with terminal cancer, proposes a 'final solution' to a startled Jenna. Patsy and Dawn's relationship comes to a head.

summaries.short: (Season One Finale) Dr. James' plans change; Patsy goes the distance with Dawn; DiDi recovers a debt.
summaries.full: (Season One Finale) Phyllis (Molly Shannon), the daughter of an ailing patient, gets the travel runaround as her mother's condition worsens, improves, and worsens again. After criticizing a proposal to add men to the ward, Jenna tries to leverage her Cleveland opportunity into concessions from Dr. Stickley. Patsy goes the distance with Dawn; DiDi recovers a debt.

summaries.short: DiDi struggles with her sister; Patsy wins an award; Jenna gets a new look.
summaries.full: DiDi struggles to deal with her younger sister Sherrie, who's filling in at Billy Barnes and cozying up to Dawn. Jenna gets a new look and runs into resistance to her research methods. Patsy lets an award go to his head. The staff tries to balance patient flow and has issues discharging a patient they'd hoped to never see again.

summaries.short: A placid night shift is turned upside down by a new patient and some familiar drunken visitors.
summaries.full: DiDi's nightshift in the ward is turned upside down after the arrival of a new patient and several unwelcome, inebriated visitors. Stopping by after a (lamentable) dinner party, Dr. James attends to her drunken husband Richard's ingrown toenail; a woozy Dawn looks for stopgap comforts in the lounge; and an elderly Swedish tourist shows off her gymnastic chops.
